#Text=Jamie Hawkesworth
#Text=Jamie Hawkesworth is a British fashion and documentary photographer . [ 1 ] [ 2 ]
#Text=Hawkesworth 's first photography project was made in Preston bus station as a member of the collective Preston is My Paris . [ 3 ] [ 4 ]
#Text=The work was published in their 2010 self-published newspaper as well as in his own 2017 book , both called Preston Bus Station .
#Text=That experience has influenced his work since , [ 1 ] shooting fashion campaigns , catalogues and editorials . [ 1 ]

#Text=He has had solo exhibitions at The Hepworth Wakefield in Wakefield , UK ; Red Hook Labs in Brooklyn , New York City ; and Huis Marseille in Amsterdam ; the latter showing a mix of his personal as well as his commercial photography . [ 1 ] [ 2 ]
#Text=In 2014 the British Journal of Photography pronounced Hawkesworth " One to Watch " . [ 5 ]
#Text=In 2017 The New York Times said he is " feted as one of the most talented fashion photographers of his generation " . [ 1 ]

column1: #Text=His images have been described by I.D. as being " defined by their romantic warmth , simple beauty , and emotional openness " . [ 2 ]
#Text=In 2018 he received the Award for Editorial , Advertising and Fashion Photography , from the Royal Photographic Society .
#Text=Life and work
#Text=Hawkesworth grew up in Ipswich . [ 6 ]
#Text=He first used a camera in 2007 as part of his studies for a forensic science degree at the University of Central Lancashire in Preston . [ 1 ] [ 6 ]
#Text=He subsequently switched to a photography degree , graduating in 2009 . [ 6 ]
#Text=His first completed photography project was Preston Bus Station , [ 1 ] [ 2 ]
#Text=street photography , portraits of people , and a short film made over three years in Preston bus station [ 1 ] in North West England , including one whole month spent there .
#Text=It was made as a member of the collective Preston is My Paris . [ 3 ] [ 4 ]
#Text=The photographs were included in the group 's 2010 self-published newspaper , as well as in Hawkesworth 's own 2017 monograph .
#Text=He has said of the project " it informed how I understand light , how I approach people .
#Text=Landscape with Tree , Huis Marseille , Amsterdam , 2017 . [ 2 ] [ 20 ] [ 21 ]
#Text=Various personal and commercial work including Preston Bus Station . [ 1 ]
#Text=A blue painted fence , Aylesbury Street , London , December 2018 .
#Text=Includes " film , drawings , and writing , as well as new photographs from Kenya , Louisiana and Romania " . [ 22 ]
#Text=Group exhibitions
#Text=Four Versions of Three Routes , 40 site-specific street posters at various locations , Brighton Photo Biennial , Brighton , UK , 2012 . [ 23 ]
#Text=Directed by Adam Murray and with photographs by the Preston is My Paris photographers Murray , Robert Parkinson , Hawkesworth , and Theo Simpson .
#Text=North : Identity , Photography , Fashion , Open Eye Gallery , Liverpool , UK ; [ 24 ]
#Text=North : Fashioning Identity , Somerset House , London , 2017 . [ 25 ] [ 26 ] [ 27 ]
#Text=Curated by Lou Stoppard and Adam Murray .
